28/*
29 * Parse Composite Document Files, the format used in Microsoft Office
30 * document files before they switched to zipped XML.
31 * Info from: http://sc.openoffice.org/compdocfileformat.pdf
32 *
33 * N.B. This is the "Composite Document File" format, and not the
34 * "Compound Document Format", nor the "Channel Definition Format".
35 */
36
37#ifndef _H_CDF_
38#define _H_CDF_
39
40#ifdef WIN32
41#include <winsock2.h>
42#define timespec timeval
43#define tv_nsec tv_usec
44#endif
45#ifdef __DJGPP__
46#define timespec timeval
47#define tv_nsec tv_usec
48#endif
49
50typedef int32_t cdf_secid_t;
51
52#define CDF_LOOP_LIMIT 10000
53
54#define CDF_SECID_NULL 0
55#define CDF_SECID_FREE -1
56#define CDF_SECID_END_OF_CHAIN -2
57#define CDF_SECID_SECTOR_ALLOCATION_TABLE -3
58#define CDF_SECID_MASTER_SECTOR_ALLOCATION_TABLE -4
59
60typedef struct {
61 uint64_t h_magic;
62#define CDF_MAGIC 0xE11AB1A1E011CFD0LL
63 uint64_t h_uuid[2];
64 uint16_t h_revision;
65 uint16_t h_version;
66 uint16_t h_byte_order;
67 uint16_t h_sec_size_p2;
68 uint16_t h_short_sec_size_p2;
69 uint8_t h_unused0[10];
70 uint32_t h_num_sectors_in_sat;
71 uint32_t h_secid_first_directory;
72 uint8_t h_unused1[4];
73 uint32_t h_min_size_standard_stream;
74 cdf_secid_t h_secid_first_sector_in_short_sat;
75 uint32_t h_num_sectors_in_short_sat;
76 cdf_secid_t h_secid_first_sector_in_master_sat;
77 uint32_t h_num_sectors_in_master_sat;
78 cdf_secid_t h_master_sat[436/4];
79} cdf_header_t;
80
81#define CDF_SEC_SIZE(h) CAST(size_t, 1 << (h)->h_sec_size_p2)
82#define CDF_SEC_POS(h, secid) (CDF_SEC_SIZE(h) + (secid) * CDF_SEC_SIZE(h))
83#define CDF_SHORT_SEC_SIZE(h) CAST(size_t, 1 << (h)->h_short_sec_size_p2)
84#define CDF_SHORT_SEC_POS(h, secid) ((secid) * CDF_SHORT_SEC_SIZE(h))
85
86typedef int32_t cdf_dirid_t;
87#define CDF_DIRID_NULL -1
88
89typedef int64_t cdf_timestamp_t;
90#define CDF_BASE_YEAR 1601
91#define CDF_TIME_PREC 10000000
92
93typedef struct {
94 uint16_t d_name[32];
95 uint16_t d_namelen;
96 uint8_t d_type;
97#define CDF_DIR_TYPE_EMPTY 0
98#define CDF_DIR_TYPE_USER_STORAGE 1
99#define CDF_DIR_TYPE_USER_STREAM 2
100#define CDF_DIR_TYPE_LOCKBYTES 3
101#define CDF_DIR_TYPE_PROPERTY 4
102#define CDF_DIR_TYPE_ROOT_STORAGE 5
103 uint8_t d_color;
104#define CDF_DIR_COLOR_READ 0
105#define CDF_DIR_COLOR_BLACK 1
106 cdf_dirid_t d_left_child;
107 cdf_dirid_t d_right_child;
108 cdf_dirid_t d_storage;
109 uint64_t d_storage_uuid[2];
110 uint32_t d_flags;
111 cdf_timestamp_t d_created;
112 cdf_timestamp_t d_modified;
113 cdf_secid_t d_stream_first_sector;
114 uint32_t d_size;
115 uint32_t d_unused0;
116} cdf_directory_t;
117
118#define CDF_DIRECTORY_SIZE 128
119
120typedef struct {
121 cdf_secid_t *sat_tab;
122 size_t sat_len;
123} cdf_sat_t;
124
125typedef struct {
126 cdf_directory_t *dir_tab;
127 size_t dir_len;
128} cdf_dir_t;
129
130typedef struct {
131 void *sst_tab;
132 size_t sst_len; /* Number of sectors */
133 size_t sst_dirlen; /* Directory sector size */
134 size_t sst_ss; /* Sector size */
135} cdf_stream_t;
136
137typedef struct {
138 uint32_t cl_dword;
139 uint16_t cl_word[2];
140 uint8_t cl_two[2];
141 uint8_t cl_six[6];
142} cdf_classid_t;
143
144typedef struct {
145 uint16_t si_byte_order;
146 uint16_t si_zero;
147 uint16_t si_os_version;
148 uint16_t si_os;
149 cdf_classid_t si_class;
150 uint32_t si_count;
151} cdf_summary_info_header_t;
152
153#define CDF_SECTION_DECLARATION_OFFSET 0x1c
154
155typedef struct {
156 cdf_classid_t sd_class;
157 uint32_t sd_offset;
158} cdf_section_declaration_t;
159
160typedef struct {
161 uint32_t sh_len;
162 uint32_t sh_properties;
163} cdf_section_header_t;
164
165typedef struct {
166 uint32_t pi_id;
167 uint32_t pi_type;
168 union {
169 uint16_t _pi_u16;
170 int16_t _pi_s16;
171 uint32_t _pi_u32;
172 int32_t _pi_s32;
173 uint64_t _pi_u64;
174 int64_t _pi_s64;
175 cdf_timestamp_t _pi_tp;
176 float _pi_f;
177 double _pi_d;
178 struct {
179 uint32_t s_len;
180 const char *s_buf;
181 } _pi_str;
182 } pi_val;
183#define pi_u64 pi_val._pi_u64
184#define pi_s64 pi_val._pi_s64
185#define pi_u32 pi_val._pi_u32
186#define pi_s32 pi_val._pi_s32
187#define pi_u16 pi_val._pi_u16
188#define pi_s16 pi_val._pi_s16
189#define pi_f pi_val._pi_f
190#define pi_d pi_val._pi_d
191#define pi_tp pi_val._pi_tp
192#define pi_str pi_val._pi_str
193} cdf_property_info_t;
194
195#define CDF_ROUND(val, by) (((val) + (by) - 1) & ~((by) - 1))
196
197/* Variant type definitions */
198#define CDF_EMPTY 0x00000000
199#define CDF_NULL 0x00000001
200#define CDF_SIGNED16 0x00000002
201#define CDF_SIGNED32 0x00000003
202#define CDF_FLOAT 0x00000004
203#define CDF_DOUBLE 0x00000005
204#define CDF_CY 0x00000006
205#define CDF_DATE 0x00000007
206#define CDF_BSTR 0x00000008
207#define CDF_DISPATCH 0x00000009
208#define CDF_ERROR 0x0000000a
209#define CDF_BOOL 0x0000000b
210#define CDF_VARIANT 0x0000000c
211#define CDF_UNKNOWN 0x0000000d
212#define CDF_DECIMAL 0x0000000e
213#define CDF_SIGNED8 0x00000010
214#define CDF_UNSIGNED8 0x00000011
215#define CDF_UNSIGNED16 0x00000012
216#define CDF_UNSIGNED32 0x00000013
217#define CDF_SIGNED64 0x00000014
218#define CDF_UNSIGNED64 0x00000015
219#define CDF_INT 0x00000016
220#define CDF_UINT 0x00000017
221#define CDF_VOID 0x00000018
222#define CDF_HRESULT 0x00000019
223#define CDF_PTR 0x0000001a
224#define CDF_SAFEARRAY 0x0000001b
225#define CDF_CARRAY 0x0000001c
226#define CDF_USERDEFINED 0x0000001d
227#define CDF_LENGTH32_STRING 0x0000001e
228#define CDF_LENGTH32_WSTRING 0x0000001f
229#define CDF_FILETIME 0x00000040
230#define CDF_BLOB 0x00000041
231#define CDF_STREAM 0x00000042
232#define CDF_STORAGE 0x00000043
233#define CDF_STREAMED_OBJECT 0x00000044
234#define CDF_STORED_OBJECT 0x00000045
235#define CDF_BLOB_OBJECT 0x00000046
236#define CDF_CLIPBOARD 0x00000047
237#define CDF_CLSID 0x00000048
238#define CDF_VECTOR 0x00001000
239#define CDF_ARRAY 0x00002000
240#define CDF_BYREF 0x00004000
241#define CDF_RESERVED 0x00008000
242#define CDF_ILLEGAL 0x0000ffff
243#define CDF_ILLEGALMASKED 0x00000fff
244#define CDF_TYPEMASK 0x00000fff
245
246#define CDF_PROPERTY_CODE_PAGE 0x00000001
247#define CDF_PROPERTY_TITLE 0x00000002
248#define CDF_PROPERTY_SUBJECT 0x00000003
249#define CDF_PROPERTY_AUTHOR 0x00000004
250#define CDF_PROPERTY_KEYWORDS 0x00000005
251#define CDF_PROPERTY_COMMENTS 0x00000006
252#define CDF_PROPERTY_TEMPLATE 0x00000007
253#define CDF_PROPERTY_LAST_SAVED_BY 0x00000008
254#define CDF_PROPERTY_REVISION_NUMBER 0x00000009
255#define CDF_PROPERTY_TOTAL_EDITING_TIME 0x0000000a
256#define CDF_PROPERTY_LAST_PRINTED 0X0000000b
257#define CDF_PROPERTY_CREATE_TIME 0x0000000c
258#define CDF_PROPERTY_LAST_SAVED_TIME 0x0000000d
259#define CDF_PROPERTY_NUMBER_OF_PAGES 0x0000000e
260#define CDF_PROPERTY_NUMBER_OF_WORDS 0x0000000f
261#define CDF_PROPERTY_NUMBER_OF_CHARACTERS 0x00000010
262#define CDF_PROPERTY_THUMBNAIL 0x00000011
263#define CDF_PROPERTY_NAME_OF_APPLICATION 0x00000012
264#define CDF_PROPERTY_SECURITY 0x00000013
265#define CDF_PROPERTY_LOCALE_ID 0x80000000
266
267typedef struct {
268 int i_fd;
269 const unsigned char *i_buf;
270 size_t i_len;
271} cdf_info_t;
272
273
274typedef struct {
275 uint16_t ce_namlen;
276 uint32_t ce_num;
277 uint64_t ce_timestamp;
278 uint16_t ce_name[256];
279} cdf_catalog_entry_t;
280
281typedef struct {
282 size_t cat_num;
283 cdf_catalog_entry_t cat_e[1];
284} cdf_catalog_t;
